    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Please note it's only problem with v4 MEW, v3 works just fine.\r\nI don't think it's a problem with  ethereumjs/ethereumjs-tx#57 since the tx actually goes thru, it's the problem that MEW v4 can't get tx object after it's published, in order to get the hash...my guess it doesn't correctly construct the requests after TX has been sent since the PORT is 8545 and URL is https://... and the fact it only handles the request if `/` is provided at the end of the RPC_URL.\r\n\r\n@tayvano \r\nHave you had a chance to go over our PR https://github.com/kvhnuke/etherwallet/pull/1427\r\nWe really don't want scammers to spin out new MEW sites with wallet.poa.networkS, wallet.poaa.network, etc, etc....",
